node.text: Listening to your interview with @sarahmarieliddle gave me the confidence to raise the topic with my husband. We've been married for 11 years but together for over 20. We've been exploring ways for me to embrace my polyamory ❤️ thank you

Found your account through the @wildflowersex crappiness that was coming out. But it exposed me such incredible sex wellness content creators! I’m currently listening to your podcast about the clitoris and your voice is so soothing! Love what you do ♥️
love yourself deeply; it is the greatest revenge ✨ photo of me by @yael_malka for the @nytimes !(link in bio)
These words are amazing and you are so, so stunning 🌼

My friend @sunnybyrdbotanicals joined her husband on his podcast @byrdbrainshow to talk about their progression from monogamy to polyamory. It’s such a brilliant (2 part) conversation. Recommending to you as a peer in this work. They discuss radical honesty and self love. Proud of you and them.

@little_wildheart read Sex at Dawn by Chris Ryan & Cacilda Jetha. Incredible book that really goes into detail about monogamy & how it’s not how humans actually evolved to function. Lots of geeky anthropology goodness in it!
@little_wildheart I have an episode on @podcast_withapurpose about being poly. It’s the one with my guest James, he speaks on it in depth if you want to give it a listen!

@little_wildheart if I may...consider the ways you need to give and receive love. If those ways include "I am the only person for you and you are the only person for me", "sacrificing other intimate relationships is important for our relationship", etc., you're likely monogamous. If none of that has anything to do with how you give or receive love, you may be polyamorous or open to it. Either way (or neither way) is valid and fine! 💕💕
How do you know if you’re poly?... I think maybe I am, but maybe I’m just trying to avoid something? Any tips?
Living for your glow up! 🙌🏽🙌🏽🙌🏽
Congratulations!!!!
Aaahhh! Congrats on this Ev’Yan! You are on 🔥🔥🔥
NYT!! That’s major, can’t wait to read 😊
Beautiful 💕 what an interesting and informative article too.

It would be rad if you checked out my blog. Recent post is about diversity in public libraries. Link in my bio. I love the rawness and ability to educate and I hope my words sounds and transfer the same way. Raw and unapologetic :)
Such an inspiration ❤️
"I never opted into monogamy ... it was automatically assigned to me like straightness." OOOF. That hit me hard in a wonderful way 🌈💛
that caption 👏👏
Loved this article
So powerful! Your image and gaze, and the words 💜
This means a lot to me. Thank you for your work and for being you, Ev’Yan. I’m grateful for you!
Gorgeous.
This is #gold 💛💛💛

Photo by Ev’Yan Whitney • she/they on August 13, 2019. Image may contain: plant, flower, outdoor and nature, possible text that says 'When the sexuality doula Ev'Yan Whitney's husband told told her he was polyamorous, her first reaction was: "If you love someone else, how can you love me?" Eventually, she "realized that, like, never opted in into monogamy, that it was automatically assigned to me, like straightness." Yael Malka for The New York Times'
